<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss version="2.0"><channel><title>Conteúdo de fisl12 marcado com a tag "sound"</title><link>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12</link><description>Conteúdo de fisl12 marcado com a tag "sound"</description><item><title>Workshop guide Free Software utilization to sound editing</title><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;The sound editing was a workshop theme in the first day of 12th International Forum of Free Softwares, on this Wednesday, 29th. Approximately 40 people watched and received orientations about how to work with digital sound in open code platforms. The workshop was divided in two parts, administered by Deivi Kuhn and Lucas Santos, organizers of fisl12 who use these kind of programs to their personal productions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;At the first moment, Deivi's speech had expertise information about sound production and editing, as the correct utilization of equalization and compression tools. While he was giving the orientations on the screen, the listeners followed the exercises in their laptops, after downloading the program. The majority of the listeners already had experience or curiosity about the topic. The second part of the speech, administered by Lucas Santos, was about sound manipulation in Linux. He taught the utilization of various free softwares and showed pieces  that were compatible with tha free platform.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"&gt;Workshops in different surfaces will be ministered until the end of the event, on Saturday. Everyone who is registered on fisl12 is allowed to participate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 30 Jun 2011 16:47:35 +0000</pubDate><link>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12/fisl12/noticias/workshop-guide-free-software-utilization-to-sound-editing</link><guid>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12/fisl12/noticias/workshop-guide-free-software-utilization-to-sound-editing</guid></item></channel></rss>